                <p><span class="bigRed">No purchase necessary to enter or win. Void where prohibited.</span></p>
                
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>TopCoder, Inc. will be conducting a contest for members during the 2007 TopCoder Collegiate Challenge (TCCC07).  As a result of this contest, three members and the top three nominated professors will be awarded with a trip to attend the onsite finals of the TCCC07 in October 2007.</p>
                
                <a name="eligibility"></a>
                <h2>Eligibility</h2>
                <p>To be eligible for the contest, you must be:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>18 years of age or older; and</li>
                        <li>A registered, rated, and active member of TopCoder in good standing.</li>
                    </ul>
                <p>The 2007 TopCoder Collegiate Challenge Prestigious Professor Award Nomination is void in the Quebec province of Canada and where prohibited by applicable law. Residents of Cuba, Iran, North Korea, Sudan, or Syria are ineligible to participate and are ineligible to attend the onsite event as winners.</p>
                <p>Employees of TopCoder, Inc., their affiliated companies, advertising and promotion agencies and immediate family members of each are not eligible. Employees of any TCCC07 sponsoring companies are allowed to compete in the 2007 TopCoder Collegiate Challenge Prestigious Professor Award Nomination, provided they meet the eligibility requirements.  All federal, state and local laws and regulations apply. Void where prohibited.</p>
                
                <h2>To Enter</h2>
                <p>If not already a member, register for TopCoder electronically at <a target="_blank" href="/">www.topcoder.com</a>.  Once registered at TopCoder, submit <a target="_blank" href="/reg">here</a>.</p>
                
                <h2>Eligible Professor</h2>
                <p>To be considered an eligible professor, nominees must be an instructor in an IT or Design field including, but not limited to, Computer Science, Statistical Mathematics, Applied Mathematics, Software Engineering, Computer Engineering, Management Information Systems (MIS), Computer Information Systems (CIS), and Graphic Design.</p>
                
                <a name="winner"></a>
                <h2>Selection of Winner</h2>
                <p>The top ten (10) nominated professors will be selected by a review panel of TopCoder staff and named as finalists. Those finalists will then be posted on the TopCoder website for the community to vote for the three (3) candidates they feel deserve to go to the TCCC.</p>
                <p>Submissions will be accepted from August 13, 2007 through September 21, 2007.</p>
                <p>Online voting will take place from September 24 - 25, 2007.</p>
                <p>In order for professors to be eligible for the contest, they must be available to travel to the United States October 30 - November 2, 2007.</p>
                
                <a name="prize"></a>
                <h2>Prize</h2>
                <p>Three (3) students and their nominated professors will be awarded a trip to attend the onsite finals of the 2007 TopCoder Collegiate Challenge.  TopCoder will provide travel arrangements for winning members and professors (collectively "winners"). TopCoder will provide ground transportation to and from the airport, as well as hotel accommodations and certain meals. All other expenses are the responsibility of the winners. TopCoder will not provide travel or lodging accommodations for a guest to accompany the winners to the 2007 TopCoder Collegiate Challenge.  Winners accept responsibility for all federal, state, and local taxes and fees in connection with the prize.</p>
                
